main event: On January 6, 1958, three unidentified objects with blinking lights were observed in Dayton, Ohio, believed to be landing lights from a mysterious car.
interesting points: The observation occurred at dusk at 6:00 A.M.,Three objects were seen but their course was considered inconsistent due to the eccentricity of the source,The objects were thought to be landing lights of a vehicle, there were varying conclusions about what the objects could have been,Including a balloon or visual phenomenon,No photographs were included in the report.
sighted object: three unidentified objects with blinking lights
witness description: Witness believed the lights were from a 'mysterious' car
